> Another work day, another dinner daydream. This dish is perfect for when you're
> sitting at your desk and suddenly all you can think is, "Dinner...what the heck
> am I going to eat for dinner?!" We've got you covered with seared pork
> cutlets, zesty rice, and a cucumber and candied peanut salad, drizzled with a
> spicy-sweet chili-lime glaze.

Wash and dry all produce. Trim and halve @Persian cucumber{1}; thinly slice
crosswise into half-moons. Zest and halve @lime{1}. Pat @pork cutlets{12%ounce}
dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a large, dry pan over medium-high heat. Add @peanuts{1/2%ounce}; cook,
stirring, until lightly browned, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add @sugar{1%tsp} and @water{1%tbsp}. Cook, stirring, until peanuts are coated
and tacky, ~{1-2%minutes}. Turn off heat; remove from pan and set aside. Wash
out pan.

Once cool enough to handle, roughly chop peanuts.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tsp} in same pan over high heat. Add pork
and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{} and set aside. Wipe out pan.

While pork cooks, using your hands, massage @microwaveable jasmine rice{1}
in package to break up grains.

Heat a medium pan over medium heat. Add rice and @water{2%tbsp}. Cook, stirring,
until warmed through, ~{2-3%minutes}. Stir in @butter{1%tbsp} and season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}. Remove pan from heat.

Heat pan used for pork over medium-low heat; add @sweet Thai chili sauce{2%ounce}
and a squeeze of lime juice.

Return pork to pan and turn to coat in glaze. Turn off heat.

== Cucumber Peanut Salad ==

In a large #bowl{}, whisk together juice from remaining lime, @olive oil{1.5%tbsp},
and a pinch of sugar.

Toss in @mixed greens{2%ounce}, cucumber, and peanuts. Season with salt and
pepper.

== To Serve ==

Stir lime zest and a pinch of salt into bowl with rice.

Divide rice between plates and top with pork and any remaining glaze. Serve
with salad on the side.